#Text=The Toronto Raptors ( 29 - 15 ) defeated the Detroit Pistons ( 17 - 28 ) 114 - 110 on Sunday at the Air Canada Center in Toronto .
#Text=Despite being out - scored 31 - 25 in the final quarter , the Raptors were able to hold of the Pistons ' late comeback attempt and secure the four - point victory in front of their home crowd .
#Text=While the game may have been close , the Raptors shot the ball much better than the Pistons , going 53 percent from the field compared to just 46 percent from the field for the Pistons .
#Text=The Raptors also forced them into 14 turnovers , while only committing eight of their own , which may have made a big difference in this one .

#Text=After combining for only 14 points over his last three games , DeMar DeRozan returned to form Sunday , finishing with 25 points ( 8 - 14 FG , 1 - 2 3Pt , 8 - 10 FT ) , six rebounds and four assists .
#Text=It was good to see him turn things around , as the Raptors really needed him to play well after losing six of their last ten games .
#Text=Jonas Valnciunas was another big factor in the win .
#Text=He went 9 - for - 15 from the field and 2 - for - 2 from the free throw line to score 20 points , while adding 11 rebounds and three blocked shots as well .
#Text=He 's now recorded a double - double in three out of his last four games , while also notching three blocks in two consecutive outings .
#Text=Amir Johnson had a solid showing as well , finishing with an efficient 17 points ( 7 - 9 FG , 3 - 4 FT ) and two rebounds .
#Text=He only played 17 minutes in Friday 's win over the Sixers , but he was back to a normal amount of minutes Sunday , playing a full game 's worth of 28 .
#Text=Both Greivis Vasquez and Louis Williams reached double figures in points as well , with 13 and 12 points respectively .
#Text=With Brandon Jennings going down for the year , D.J .
#Text=Augustin stepped up in a big way , going 12 - for - 20 from the field and 5 - for - 9 from the three - point line to score a game - high of 35 points , while adding eight assists as well .
#Text=It was the most shots he 's taken all season , resulting in a new season - high in points .
#Text=He 'll run as the starting point guard moving forward .
#Text=Greg Monroe had another strong stat line Sunday , recording 21 points ( 9 - 17 FG , 3 - 5 FT ) and 16 rebounds .
#Text=He 's now posted a double - double in four out of his last five games .
#Text=Andre Drummond nearly notched a double - double of his own , but came up just shy with 14 points ( 7 - 11 FG , 0 - 1 FT ) and eight rebounds .
#Text=He had a really tough matchup with Valanciunas , so he did n't have his normal eye - popping amount of rebounds that he 's come accustomed to .
#Text=The only other Piston to reach double figures in points was Kentavious Caldwell-Pope who added 16 points ( 6 - 17 FG , 3 - 9 3Pt , 1 - 2 FT ) , three rebounds and two steals .
#Text=The Raptors ' next game will be on the road against the Indiana Pacers on Tuesday , while the Pistons will be at home against the Cleveland Cavaliers on Tuesday .
